frameDefinitions: An Agent finishes an Activity, which can no longer logically continue.
An Evaluee, which can be a person or an object, has an amount of acceptability or utilization based on general (often non-aesthetic) desirability.
This frame contains nouns denoting a rank or level within an established hierarchy.
Two individuals, the Subordinate and the Superior have a relationship such that the Subordinate generally follows orders given by the Superior and has the best interests of the Superior in mind.
An Entity is well-known among a wide range of people (in general or in a particular domain) for a particular Reason, which may be a behavior, characteristic, or some other associated item.

A Behavior, attributed to an Evaluee, conforms with or is heavily influenced by a popular trend or practice, often in the realm of fashion, design, though extending social and interactional behavior in general.
frameExamples: Jason <t>completed</t> grading the papers late Sunday night.
The archduke and several of his <t><fex name='Subordinate'>henchmen</fex></t> got out of the carriage, looking around nervously.
Shakespeare was <t>famous</t> during his life because he performed in front of Queen Elizabeth I more than anyone else.
Wearing flowered brocaded silks was <t>fashionable</t> in the first few years of the decade.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the <fen>Agent</fen> who has finished an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> has finished.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> finishes.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> finishes the <fen>Activity</fen>.
The person or object that is being evaluated for its desirability.
The time when the Evaluee is judged to be desirable.
The geographic area where an <fen>Evaluee</fen> is considered desirable.
The Rank itself, usually denoted by the noun.
An entity which holds a particular <fen>Rank</fen>.
The individual in charge of the <fen>Subordinate</fen>.
The individual under the command of the <fen>Superior</fen>.
The <fen>Entity</fen> which is widely known and recognized.
The behavior, attribute, or associated entities that provide the reason for the <fen>Entity</fen> being famous.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Entity</fen> is famous.
The location where the <fen>Entity</fen> is famous.
The <fen>Evaluee</fen> is judged to conform to some degree with popular fashion with respect to his or her behavior.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Behavior</fen> is trendy or fashionable.
The location where the <fen>Behavior</fen> is trendy..
listRoleExamples: Electronica is all the rage <fex>in Europe</fex>.
This station is famous <fex>for the many ramen shacks surrounding it</fex>.
Certain people are well known <fex>only in North America</fex>.
